article.headline: S. Illinois 64, W. Michigan 46
article.story: CARBONDALE, Ill. -- Kevin Dillard came off the bench to score 16 points and add eight assists to lead Southern Illinois to a 64-46 victory over Western Michigan on Monday. Wesley Clemmons had 11 points for Southern Illinois (5-6), which led 27-22 going into halftime. The Salukis came back from the break to outscore the Broncos 37-24 in the second period. David Kool led Western Michigan with 12 points and Shawntes Gary added ten points for the Broncos. Donald Lawson had a game-high 11 rebounds and six points before he fouled out. Southern Illinois led by as many as 21 points in the second period. The Salukis scored 15 points on the Broncos' 17 turnovers. Southern Illinois also earned 28 points from its bench players. Western Michigan's shooting fell off in the second half, dropping from 45 percent in the first period to 25 percent in the second period.
